Description.Text: This is an excellent, 4-star, superior first-class hotel in a fantastic location and it is a superb choice for those visiting Paris to sightsee or shop. (IU/0707)
The hotel is located in one of the most famous avenues in Paris, a few steps from the Arc De Triomphe and close to prestigious shops, restaurants and famous Paris places.
The rooms vary in size, but are in excellent condition, with a refined décor and excellent facilities. The marble bathrooms are also in very good condition. All rooms have separate toilets.
Built by Gustave Eiffel, the hotel has impressive Parisian architecture with small wrought iron balconies on the windows.
The newly-appointed Michelin star-rated restaurant welcomes guests with a very elegant décor, where they can enjoy refined gastronomy.

The lobby is large in size, entirely decorated in typical English style, with red and green colours and furnished to a high standard. Guests can relax in elegant lounges and the public areas are very clean and bright.
